title: Frieze, 1805–15
creditline: Purchased for the Museum by the Advisory Council
description: Horizontal rectangle. Architectural moldings, and figures of two putti in a wheat field. To left and right, portions of a vertically placed quiver from which droop ears of wheat.

tombstone.epitaph:
Frieze, 1805–15.
1805–15. Block-printed, handmade paper. Purchased for the Museum by the Advisory Council. 1925-1-371.
